Materialised vs Non-Materialised
Materialized and non-materialized are two distinct categories of views. In this exercise, you will organize their differences and similarities.
Organize these characteristics into the category that they describe best.


Non-Materialised
Always return up to date data/values
Better to use on write-intensive DBs

Materialised
Consume more storage
Store query results on the disk

Materialised & Non-Materialised
Reduce overhead of writing queries
Can be used in a dwh


These characteristics can help make decisions about when to use a materialized or non-materialized view.


